title: Richard Wingfield (MP for Portsmouth)
text:
Sir Richard Wingfield (c. 1510 – 1557/59), of <a href="Portsmouth">Portsmouth</a>, <a href="Hampshire">Hampshire</a>, was an English politician.
He was a <a href="Member%20of%20Parliament">Member</a> (MP) of the <a href="Parliament%20of%20England">Parliament of England</a> for <a href="Portsmouth%20%28UK%20Parliament%20constituency%29">Portsmouth</a> in March 1553.
